          <p>Uranus is the seventh planet from the Sun and the third-largest in our solar system. This ice giant is unique for its extreme 98-degree axial tilt that causes it to roll through space on its side, creating the most extreme seasons of any planet. With a pale blue-green appearance, faint ring system, 27 moons named after literary characters, and mysteriously low internal heat, Uranus stands as one of the solar system's most peculiar worlds.</p>
