            <li><strong>Tallest Cliff:</strong> Miranda's Verona Rupes is the tallest known cliff in the solar system, plunging about 20 kilometers (12 miles). Due to Miranda's low gravity, an object dropped from the top would take about 12 minutes to hit the bottom.</li>

