            <li><strong>Only One Visitor:</strong> Voyager 2 remains the only spacecraft to visit Uranus, making it one of the least-explored planets. All our close-up knowledge of Uranus comes from observations made during a few hours in January 1986.</li>

            <li><strong>Diamond Rain:</strong> Scientists theorize that deep within Uranus (and <a href="/atlas/solar-system/neptune/">Neptune</a>), methane may be compressed into diamond crystals that rain slowly downward toward the core. Laboratory experiments have demonstrated this process is possible under the extreme pressure and temperature conditions found in ice giant interiors.</li>
